1. Time management: Improving your time-management skills can help you manage and prioritize tasks more efficiently to achieve a better work-life balance.

2. Setting boundaries: Set clear limits on when you are working and when you are not. Inform the people around you about these boundaries, so they know when they can expect your availability.

3. Prioritization: Evaluate your tasks regularly by developing a task list or using a priority matrix to judge what is most important and should be done first.

4. Learn to delegate: Share responsibilities with other team members instead of attempting to handle everything yourself, as some tasks can be handed off while still achieving desired results.

5. Scheduling breaks: Make it a point to schedule regular breaks throughout the day that allows relaxation or personal interests exploration without feeling guilty for doing them during “work hours.”
